p: In contrast, in the P4 spectra, sesquiterpene alcohols clearly predominated (49%), while the compounds detected in the previous oils ( Table 1) were present in minute quantities. Of these, high amounts of polysantol (9.2%) and javanol isomers (24.4%) were observed ( Table 2, Figure 3). Eudesmol isomers constituted only 6.1%, elemol 3.2%, and valerianol 4.7%. In addition, ebanol was present in two peaks, constituting 8.4% in total ( Table 2, Figure 3). Compared to P1–P3, a lower level of sesquiterpenes (C 15H 24) was recorded (12.9%), such as selinene (2.6%), curcumene (1.5%) and caryophyllene (0.9%). Unlike P1–P3, cadinene (1.5%) and murolene (1.4%) were also found to be present. In addition, linalool (3.6%), linalyl acetate (3.9%) and farnesyl acetate isomers (3.2%) were unique to this oil (P4).
